A Helios Airways flight from Larnaca to Athens crashed near Grammatiko, causing anger among relatives at Larnaca airport.
Reports of past decompression issues fueled suspicions of a technical fault.
Experts suggested the crew may have lost consciousness due to cabin pressure loss.
Fighter jets shadowed the plane, revealing an unconscious co-pilot.
Eyewitnesses described the tragic crash scene.
The cause remains unclear, but terrorism has been ruled out.
Condolences were expressed to the victims' families.
The crash, which killed all 121 on board, was a devastating event that left many questions unanswered.
